notes_display: In Historical Sketches of the Paper Currency of the American Colonies by Henry Phillips, Jr. (1865). Given to Dr. Jesse C. Green in 1890. Leaf 56AJ. Signed by Joseph Mifflin, future governor
issue_place_s: Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States of America
issue_obverse_legend_s: EIGHTEEN PENCE. According to an Act of General Assembly of Pennsilvania, passed in the 13th Year of the Reign of his Majesty GEORGE the Third.  Dated the 1st Day of October, 1773. Eighteen Pence.
issue_reverse_legend_s: To Counterfeit is Death. | One Shilling & Sixpence. |  Printed by HALL and SELLERS.
